France court postpones decision on extradition of ex-Kosovo PM Ramush Haradinaj 
2-3-2017 
Ramush Haradinaj, a former Kosovo prime minister, answers reporters outside the Colmar courthouse, Thursday, March 2, 2017. (AP Photo/Jean-Francois Badias) Ramush Haradinaj, a former Kosovo prime minister, answers reporters outside the Colmar courthouse, Thursday, March 2, 2017. (AP Photo/Jean-Francois Badias)

A French appeals court said on Thursday that it was postponing a decision on the possible extradition of former Kosovo prime minister Ramush Haradinaj, who was a guerrilla commander during the 1998-99 Kosovo war. Authorities had detained Haradinaj as he flew into France on Jan. 4 following a request from Serbia, which says he is a war criminal for his role in leading a guerrilla insurgency in its former southern province of Kosovo.

