The arrest further strained brittle diplomatic ties between Serbia and Kosovo, which declared independence with Western backing in 2008 and has demanded Belgrade drop its efforts to prosecute people linked to the conflict. Haradinajâ€™s Alliance for the Future of Kosovo party has urged French authorities to stop all legal actions against him. Serbia said in January it would refuse to extradite people sought by France if it failed to hand over Haradinaj. 
